  "texts": [
    "Our individual evaluation did not clearly distinguish performance of Med-PaLM 2 answers from physician-generated answers, motivating more granular evaluation, including pairwise evaluation and adversarial evaluation.",
    "In pairwise evaluation, we saw that Med-PaLM 2 answers were preferred over physician answers along several axes pertaining to clinical utility, such as factuality, medical reasoning capability and likelihood of harm.",
    "Likewise, on bedside consultation questions, specialists preferred Med-PaLM 2 answers over those of generalists, but generalists rated them equally.",
    "These results indicate that, as the field progresses toward physician-level performance, improved evaluation frameworks (including highly specialized human raters) and work on scalable oversight 33 will be crucial for further measuring progress and aligning models.",
    "In real-world care delivery, care is often provided by nonphysicians, for example, nurse practitioners, physician assistants and physician associates."
  ],
